{
  "texts": [
    "The best result from our models outperforms all baselines and surpasses the fine-tuning task by an average of 4 points, indicating the enhancement of image and text comprehension from the MoE layer.",
    "However, it is also a notable phenomenon that the MoE-Task with all datasets involved shows less capability of image understanding than the one with image data only and the one without long speech data, i.e., MoE-Task1-short and Task2.",
    "We hypothesize that this minor decrement in performance is attributed to the mixture of three modality data boosting the understanding of speech with video as well as the image content.",
    "Yet, with the presence of long speech data, our models are confused about making the right choice of expert for audio, image, and text modality, which leads to a subtle decline in performance.",
    "Overall, our models show a great ability to interact with other modalities while maintaining the ability of text-image understanding, which makes the method of mixture of experts superior in building multimodal models.Video QA: Table 6 shows the performance of our models on zero-shot tri-modality video QA tasks."
  ]
}